<section class="sleep-timeline-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center">
      <span class="section-label">Your Journey</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Your first <em>30 days.</em></h2>
      <p class="section-sub centered">Two gummies daily. Here's how your body transforms, week by week.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="sleep-timeline">

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-phase">Day 1</div>
          <h3 class="timeline-title">The loading begins</h3>
          <p class="timeline-body">You take two gummies — no powder, no shaker bottle, no chalky aftertaste. Just wild berry flavour and 3.5g of creatine monohydrate. Your muscles start absorbing it immediately. The work happening under the surface is invisible for now, but it's real.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-phase">Week 1</div>
          <h3 class="timeline-title">More in the tank</h3>
          <p class="timeline-body">Your muscles are starting to saturate with creatine phosphate. You might not see it yet, but you'll feel it — an extra rep here, a heavier set there. Your recovery between sets feels a little faster. The sessions that used to leave you flat start leaving you wanting more.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-phase">Week 2</div>
          <h3 class="timeline-title">Strength starts showing up</h3>
          <p class="timeline-body">PRs that used to be out of reach are starting to feel like warm-up weights. Your ATP recycling is firing faster, which means more power output when it counts. The pump is fuller. The endurance is longer. People at the gym start noticing you're lifting different.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-phase">Week 3</div>
          <h3 class="timeline-title">The mirror doesn't lie</h3>
          <p class="timeline-body">Muscle fullness is visible now. Creatine draws water into muscle cells, which means your muscles look bigger and feel harder — not from fat, from actual intracellular volume. You're recovering faster between sessions too. You start training more frequently without burning out.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker">
          <div class="timeline-dot timeline-dot--last"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-phase">Week 4 &amp; Beyond</div>
          <h3 class="timeline-title">The athlete you've been building</h3>
          <p class="timeline-body">Your creatine stores are fully saturated. Every session now runs on a full tank. Strength gains compound. Muscle mass grows. Recovery is faster than it's ever been. This is what consistent creatine looks like — and Gummi makes sure you never miss a dose.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.sleep-timeline-section {
  padding: 80px 24px;
  background: var(--white);
}

.sleep-timeline {
  max-width: 680px;
  margin: 56px auto 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.timeline-item {
  display: flex;
  gap: 28px;
  position: relative;
}

.timeline-marker {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  width: 24px;
}

.timeline-dot {
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--purple-deep);
  border: 3px solid var(--purple-pale);
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 4px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--purple-pale);
}

.timeline-dot--last {
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(59,31,107,0.15);
}

.timeline-line {
  flex: 1;
  width: 2px;
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--purple-light), var(--purple-pale));
  margin: 8px 0;
  min-height: 40px;
}

.timeline-content {
  padding-bottom: 48px;
  flex: 1;
}

.timeline-item:last-child .timeline-content {
  padding-bottom: 0;
}

.timeline-phase {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--purple-mid);
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}

.timeline-title {
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: 22px;
  color: var(--text-dark);
  margin-bottom: 12px;
  line-height: 1.25;
}

.timeline-body {
  font-size: 15px;
  color: var(--text-mid);
  line-height: 1.75;
}

@media(max-width: 767px) {
  .timeline-title { font-size: 19px; }
  .timeline-body { font-size: 14px; }
  .sleep-timeline { margin-top: 40px; }
}
</style>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Performance Timeline",
  "settings": [],
  "presets": [{ "name": "Performance Timeline" }]
}
{% endschema %}
